objenome.solver.evolve

Class TypedOrganism<X extends Node,Y>

  • java.lang.Object
    • objenome.solver.evolve.AbstractOrganism
      • objenome.solver.evolve.TypedOrganism<X,Y>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Comparable<Organism>, Organism
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Civilized

    public class TypedOrganism<X extends Node,Y>
extends AbstractOrganism
    An TypedOrganism is a candidate solution which uses a strongly typed tree representation to represent a computer program. This class provides several convenient methods for obtaining information about the program tree (such as size() and depth()), but more information is available directly from the tree. Use getRoot() to get access to the tree.

    Note: this class has a natural ordering that may be inconsistent with equals.

    Since:
    2.0

        public int depth()
        Returns the maximum depth of the program tree. The depth of a tree is defined as the length of the path from the root to the deepest node in the tree. For a tree with just one node (the root), the depth is 0.
        Returns:
        the maximum depth of the program tree

      • compareTo

        public int compareTo(Organism other)
        Compares this individual to another based on their fitness. It returns a negative integer, zero, or a positive integer as this instance represents the quality of an individual that is less fit, equally fit, or more fit than the specified object. The individuals do not need to be of the same object type, but must have non-null, comparable Fitness instances.
        Parameters:
        other - an individual to compare against
        Returns:
        a negative integer, zero, or a positive integer as this object is less fit than, equally fit as, or fitter than the specified object
